1
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:15,633
The child is still your family.

2
00:00:15,700 --> 00:00:17,533
He has Amanda's blood.

3
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:18,833
What's going to happen
when she gives birth?

4
00:00:18,900 --> 00:00:21,467
They won't be bringing
a child home.

5
00:00:21,533 --> 00:00:29,067
I have a plan, Zandro.

6
00:00:29,133 --> 00:00:30,633
Forgive me.

7
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:33,167
- Don't kill me.
- I changed my mind.

8
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:37,500
I don't care about
your illegal dealings.

9
00:00:37,567 --> 00:00:40,667
All I want is to get revenge.
I just want to get my daughter.

10
00:00:40,733 --> 00:00:42,567
You'll get what you want,
Amanda.

11
00:00:42,633 --> 00:00:44,333
Zandro owes me a lot.

12
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:46,400
I'm not doing this just for you.

13
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:52,000
Oh my God!

14
00:00:52,767 --> 00:00:54,100
What is that?
A baby monster?

15
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:58,133
I don't want blood in my hands.

16
00:00:58,200 --> 00:00:59,767
No one will die, Lucho.

17
00:00:59,833 --> 00:01:03,100
I just want them to feel
what they did to me.

18
00:01:03,167 --> 00:01:04,000
Rina, we have a problem.
What's the problem?

19
00:01:05,067 --> 00:01:06,333
The brake is not working!

20
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:07,400
Do something about it!

21
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:09,167
I'm on it!

22
00:01:09,433 --> 00:01:10,600
Oh my God!

23
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:14,133
Forgive me, Eden, for
what I'm about to do.

24
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:16,933
But I'm doing all
of this for you.

25
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:20,667
To get you away from
the people you trust.

26
00:01:20,733 --> 00:01:22,667
Eden, your baby.

27
00:01:23,267 --> 00:01:24,333
Your baby's gone.

28
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:25,700
- It's gone.
- That's not true.

29
00:01:25,767 --> 00:01:27,100
I heard my baby cry.

30
00:01:27,167 --> 00:01:28,133
- Let me see my baby.
- Your baby's gone.

31
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:29,133
It's gone!

32
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:31,667
The baby's gone!

33
00:01:31,733 --> 00:01:32,533
How did that happen?
She's not due to
give birth yet.

34
00:01:33,433 --> 00:01:35,533
She's only in her eight-month.

35
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:37,567
Can someone tell me
what's happening?

36
00:01:37,633 --> 00:01:39,167
How's our baby doing?

37
00:01:39,233 --> 00:01:40,733
The baby's gone, Red.

38
00:01:40,833 --> 00:01:41,967
The baby's dead.

39
00:01:42,033 --> 00:01:43,133
No!

40
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:45,667
- Red, Red!
- No!

41
00:01:45,733 --> 00:01:48,833
Red.

42
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:49,667
No!

43
00:01:50,933 --> 00:01:53,033
I got rid of the baby.

44
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:58,533
Now, Red and Eden have
a chance to break up.

45
00:02:10,367 --> 00:02:14,533
I took care of the baby's
funeral service already.

46
00:02:15,100 --> 00:02:17,100
I'll tell them
about it later.

47
00:02:18,433 --> 00:02:20,200
How is your son doing?

48
00:02:22,633 --> 00:02:25,967
Of course, he's sad.

49
00:02:27,100 --> 00:02:29,000
He didn't see this coming.

50
00:02:29,067 --> 00:02:32,633
I mean, honestly,
Eden and the baby

51
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:35,333
were in the best of health.

52
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:43,833
I'm here to get some stuff.

53
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:45,467
I'm going straight back
to the hospital.

54
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,733
How are you, Son?

55
00:02:48,633 --> 00:02:49,567
How are you?

56
00:02:53,133 --> 00:02:55,267
Yenyen can't still
accept what happened.

57
00:02:57,733 --> 00:02:58,967
It's hard to accept.

58
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:02,200
I don't know why it
has to happen to us.

59
00:03:02,267 --> 00:03:07,433
I think Amanda cursed
the two of you.

60
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:09,600
And the baby.

61
00:03:09,667 --> 00:03:12,167
Can you imagine? She sent
a dead fetus.

62
00:03:12,233 --> 00:03:14,000
Come on. Who in the right mind

63
00:03:14,067 --> 00:03:15,600
will think of something
like that?

64
00:03:15,667 --> 00:03:17,333
She's so evil!

65
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,067
Rina.

66
00:03:18,133 --> 00:03:19,100
That's enough.

67
00:03:19,833 --> 00:03:24,233
From now on, we'll only say
encouraging words, right?

68
00:03:24,333 --> 00:03:27,433
Red, you know it's not
the end of everything.

69
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:28,267
You guys are still young.

70
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:30,467
You can have another baby,
right?

71
00:03:30,533 --> 00:03:31,300
Hold on.

72
00:03:31,367 --> 00:03:33,133
Come on, we're still mourning.

73
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,700
Make another baby? Really?

74
00:03:35,767 --> 00:03:37,433
That's your advice?

75
00:03:46,333 --> 00:03:48,033
What are you doing, Victor?

76
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:50,800
There's so much advice
you can give him.

77
00:03:50,867 --> 00:03:53,367
Why do you have to tell
him to make another baby?

78
00:03:53,433 --> 00:03:54,400
Come on.

79
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:58,200
I just said that to make
your son feel better.

80
00:03:59,467 --> 00:04:01,067
We just got rid of a problem.

81
00:04:01,133 --> 00:04:03,133
Now you want to create
another one.

82
00:04:20,233 --> 00:04:22,100
Red, my vitamins.

83
00:04:22,433 --> 00:04:23,833
What time is it?

84
00:04:29,467 --> 00:04:31,700
I forgot I'm not
pregnant anymore.

85
00:04:32,767 --> 00:04:34,500
I don't have a baby anymore.

86
00:04:38,033 --> 00:04:39,500
Why did this happen, Red?

87
00:04:40,667 --> 00:04:44,000
Why did I have to
hear the baby's cry?

88
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:47,333
Only to end up losing him?

89
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:55,033
I guess we should just think...

90
00:04:55,100 --> 00:04:57,733
there's a reason the baby
was taken from us.

91
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:02,333
I don't want to ask
questions anymore.

92
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:06,100
No one can give me
the answer anyway.

93
00:05:07,267 --> 00:05:10,333
Don't you think God
is punishing me?

94
00:05:10,933 --> 00:05:13,100
Because I disobeyed my mom.

95
00:05:15,967 --> 00:05:17,800
Don't say that.

96
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,867
God didn't want this to happen.

97
00:05:24,933 --> 00:05:26,267
Your mom did.

98
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,800
Your mom wanted this to happen.

99
00:05:30,433 --> 00:05:32,233
She's the one to blame.

100
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:39,067
I don't know how
she could do that.

101
00:05:39,133 --> 00:05:40,733
Your own mom.

102
00:05:44,833 --> 00:05:49,800
Doesn't she know that your
baby has her blood too?

103
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,867
She's so evil.

104
00:05:54,567 --> 00:05:57,667
I don't know what to say, Red.

105
00:05:58,200 --> 00:06:03,333
It had already hurt me so much
when she considered me dead.

106
00:06:04,767 --> 00:06:08,167
And she still didn't
spare our baby, Red.

107
00:06:14,967 --> 00:06:16,333
Don't worry.

108
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:23,300
Don't be discouraged.

109
00:06:25,067 --> 00:06:28,333
What matters is
we're still here.

110
00:06:29,333 --> 00:06:31,233
We still love each other.

111
00:06:31,867 --> 00:06:33,700
That's what matters.

112
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:35,733
Okay?

113
00:07:13,267 --> 00:07:14,100
Eden...

114
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:20,933
Eden, let's put your
baby in the columbarium.

115
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:21,200
Okay?

116
00:07:22,867 --> 00:07:26,000
Auntie, can the baby
stay with me...

117
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,733
for a few days?

118
00:07:30,033 --> 00:07:32,867
I want to keep him with me.

119
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:37,767
Yeah, we can request for that.

120
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:41,967
He can stay here until we bring
him to his final resting place.

121
00:07:46,433 --> 00:07:47,400
Eden...

122
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:57,333
Eden, I know how painful
it is to lose a child.

123
00:07:58,367 --> 00:08:00,000
We went through the same thing.

124
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:02,567
I lost a child too.

125
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:07,133
But what I can't accept is...

126
00:08:08,367 --> 00:08:14,467
that Amanda did this
to both of us.

127
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,900
What kind of joke is this?

128
00:08:19,333 --> 00:08:21,600
It's painful for all of us.

129
00:08:22,533 --> 00:08:27,300
But if it's up to me, I want
Amanda to pay for this.

130
00:08:27,367 --> 00:08:28,800
She needs to go back to jail.

131
00:08:28,867 --> 00:08:29,900
Serves her right!

132
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:30,867
She has to!

133
00:08:30,933 --> 00:08:33,567
After everything she
did to our family!

134
00:08:33,633 --> 00:08:35,867
- Auntie.
- What is it, Eden?

135
00:08:35,933 --> 00:08:37,833
Are you going to defend
your mother again?

136
00:08:38,933 --> 00:08:42,333
Didn't she do enough
damage to our family?

137
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:46,000
Eden, she doesn't love you.

138
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:50,233
She doesn't love you.

139
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:53,867
She harmed my grandchild too!

140
00:08:55,167 --> 00:08:57,100
Mom, stop!

141
00:08:57,167 --> 00:08:59,167
Can you not reprimand her?

142
00:09:00,267 --> 00:09:01,067
Rina.

143
00:09:01,567 --> 00:09:02,633
Calm yourself.

144
00:09:05,433 --> 00:09:08,300
Let Eden recover first.

145
00:09:08,367 --> 00:09:10,500
Amanda's the one to blame.

146
00:09:11,667 --> 00:09:14,100
You shouldn't talk
to Eden like this.

147
00:09:18,467 --> 00:09:19,400
Come on, Yen.

148
00:09:42,300 --> 00:09:44,700
It's just a matter
of time, Rina.

149
00:09:46,867 --> 00:09:49,133
I'm getting ready
for my return.

150
00:09:52,567 --> 00:09:57,700
You'll pay for all the
abuse you did to me.

151
00:10:01,733 --> 00:10:02,967
Oh my God, Auntie.

152
00:10:03,033 --> 00:10:05,100
Red and Yenyen's
baby died?

153
00:10:06,167 --> 00:10:07,600
That's so sad.

154
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,767
Well, how's Red?

155
00:10:10,567 --> 00:10:13,767
Oh, he's not okay.

156
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:16,267
But he's recovering.

157
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:18,567
Well, so...

158
00:10:18,633 --> 00:10:22,033
does this mean that
their wedding is off?

159
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:23,633
Because that's the only reason

160
00:10:23,700 --> 00:10:26,400
why they want to get married in
the first place, right?

161
00:10:26,733 --> 00:10:31,100
If it's up to me,
the wedding is off.

162
00:10:32,633 --> 00:10:33,833
He proposed, yes.

163
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:36,133
But that's only how
far they can go.

164
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:39,100
Well, that's good
news, Auntie.

165
00:10:39,167 --> 00:10:41,167
It means that Red
is still single.

166
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:47,333
That's why you have to do
your best, Sabina, please.

167
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:53,167
Remember, a pretty face has
nothing against a flirty woman.

168
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:55,900
I know, Auntie. Cheers!

169
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:12,267
Yeah, she's here.

170
00:11:14,467 --> 00:11:15,667
Yen...

171
00:11:16,233 --> 00:11:18,833
Raichu wants to talk to you.

172
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:27,733
Hello, Raichu.

173
00:11:29,667 --> 00:11:32,433
She's not ready to
talk to anyone yet.

174
00:11:33,167 --> 00:11:34,100
Don't worry.

175
00:11:34,167 --> 00:11:36,200
She'll call you when
she's ready to talk.

176
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:39,000
Okay.

177
00:11:44,767 --> 00:11:45,900
Yen.

178
00:11:47,867 --> 00:11:49,467
You can't live like this.

179
00:11:50,867 --> 00:11:52,167
You don't eat.

180
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:55,767
You don't get out of this room.

181
00:11:57,767 --> 00:11:59,533
You don't talk to people.

182
00:12:00,133 --> 00:12:01,467
You don't talk to me.

183
00:12:04,367 --> 00:12:06,767
What can I do to
make you happy?

184
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:33,467
I want my baby, Red.

185
00:12:38,667 --> 00:12:40,933
I want to see my baby.

186
00:12:43,233 --> 00:12:46,700
I didn't even get to see him.

187
00:12:49,833 --> 00:12:52,433
I didn't even get to hug him.

188
00:12:55,067 --> 00:12:58,133
I don't even know
what he looks like.

189
00:13:04,267 --> 00:13:08,500
So, please, just leave me be.

190
00:13:10,767 --> 00:13:12,600
I just want to hug our baby,

191
00:13:12,667 --> 00:13:16,400
even though he's nothing
but ash.

192
00:14:23,033 --> 00:14:24,067
Where have you been?

193
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,267
I went to Rina's place.

194
00:14:29,033 --> 00:14:29,867
What happened?

195
00:14:31,033 --> 00:14:32,033
Did they see you?

196
00:14:33,633 --> 00:14:34,667
Did you talk to
your daughter?

197
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:39,300
I didn't show myself.

198
00:14:42,433 --> 00:14:43,267
Good.

199
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:47,700
Nothing can
ruin our plans.

200
00:14:48,233 --> 00:14:50,467
Not even your love
for your daughter.

201
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:52,767
I know.

202
00:14:53,933 --> 00:14:55,400
I love Eden.

203
00:14:55,933 --> 00:14:59,233
But love is not enough
to get her back.

204
00:15:00,233 --> 00:15:03,000
I need to use force.

205
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:14,867
Amanda's coming to haunt Rina.

206
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:39,033
Good morning, Ma'am.

207
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:40,600
Hey, good morning.

208
00:15:41,167 --> 00:15:43,533
I am after some bags, okay?

209
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:45,100
I want...

210
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:49,533
Do you have the Alfreda
crocodile skin bag,

211
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:50,767
limited edition?

212
00:15:50,833 --> 00:15:51,600
No, Ma'am.

213
00:15:51,667 --> 00:15:52,700
It's sold out.

214
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:55,967
Are you sure?

215
00:15:59,167 --> 00:16:02,300
What about the Bayton
urban satchel?

216
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,833
Sorry, Ma'am, that
one's been sold too.

217
00:16:06,367 --> 00:16:07,700
Come on.

218
00:16:08,733 --> 00:16:12,067
Okay, I'll just get
the lady crocodile bag.

219
00:16:12,133 --> 00:16:13,100
I'll settle with that.

220
00:16:13,167 --> 00:16:14,767
Sorry, Ma'am, that
one's sold too.

221
00:16:14,833 --> 00:16:16,400
All of them got
sold just earlier.

222
00:16:17,367 --> 00:16:18,700
Wait a minute,
that's three bags.

223
00:16:18,767 --> 00:16:21,400
Those bags were sold
all in one day?

224
00:16:21,467 --> 00:16:22,900
- It's sold out?
- Yes, Ma'am.

225
00:16:22,967 --> 00:16:25,800
Only one client bought
all the bags you wanted.

226
00:16:27,133 --> 00:16:29,967
Just one person bought
all of those bags?

227
00:16:32,067 --> 00:16:33,200
Who is this client?

228
00:16:33,267 --> 00:16:35,200
It's Mrs. Madrigal.

229
00:16:36,567 --> 00:16:38,000
Mrs. Madrigal, who?

230
00:16:38,567 --> 00:16:40,967
She's a new client.

231
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:48,400
Because I never heard of a
Mrs. Madrigal shopping here.

232
00:16:51,867 --> 00:16:53,000
Mrs. Madrigal.

233
00:16:56,367 --> 00:16:57,633
Who are you?

234
00:17:07,033 --> 00:17:08,067
Uncle.

235
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,167
Hey, Red.

236
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:14,867
I just want to thank you for
bringing Eden to the hospital.

237
00:17:16,767 --> 00:17:17,933
Don't mention it, Red.

238
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,967
You and Eden are family.

239
00:17:23,467 --> 00:17:25,167
I'm worried about her.

240
00:17:26,233 --> 00:17:29,800
She still can't accept
the death of our baby.

241
00:17:31,333 --> 00:17:37,167
Sometimes she says she
can hear our baby's cries.

242
00:17:40,533 --> 00:17:42,033
I don't know what happened.

243
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:43,667
You were there, right?

244
00:17:44,300 --> 00:17:45,833
Can you tell me what happened?

245
00:17:51,167 --> 00:17:55,400
Red, the baby was
alive for a second.

246
00:17:55,467 --> 00:17:57,467
And then he died.

247
00:17:58,100 --> 00:18:00,967
Your mom and I did
everything we could.

248
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:06,467
We got in an accident
because we were rushing.

249
00:18:06,533 --> 00:18:08,733
So we didn't make
it to the hospital.

250
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:13,433
Do you have a picture
of my baby?

251
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:15,700
I didn't get to see him.

252
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:18,600
I want to see his
picture, at least.

253
00:18:19,233 --> 00:18:22,433
I have none, Red.

254
00:18:22,533 --> 00:18:23,900
We were panicking.

255
00:18:31,867 --> 00:18:33,667
I'm just wondering.

256
00:18:34,533 --> 00:18:36,033
If you panicked,

257
00:18:36,100 --> 00:18:39,033
how come you still got to
bring her to a midwife?

258
00:18:39,100 --> 00:18:42,667
What a coincidence that
there was a midwife

259
00:18:42,733 --> 00:18:44,200
where you had a car accident.

260
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:46,933
That's true.

261
00:18:47,567 --> 00:18:52,700
We were just lucky
to find a midwife.

262
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:54,300
We were so lucky.

263
00:18:57,633 --> 00:18:58,700
Thank you, Uncle.

264
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:18,467
Hi, Hon.

265
00:19:22,467 --> 00:19:24,433
What are you so busy with?

266
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:26,700
I'm so excited
about this, Hon.

267
00:19:27,667 --> 00:19:30,400
I'm going to venture
into a new business.

268
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:32,267
There'll be a big profit, so...

269
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,000
I'm sure you'll like this.

270
00:19:34,067 --> 00:19:34,933
I'm pretty sure,

271
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,133
especially if it will
make us money.

272
00:19:39,133 --> 00:19:40,033
Tell me about it.

273
00:19:40,367 --> 00:19:42,000
Emma, can I have
some water, please?

274
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:46,133
Well, it's a new
investment scheme.

275
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:48,767
And I talked to the
business owner earlier.

276
00:19:48,833 --> 00:19:51,233
Mr. Lucho Madrigal.

277
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:54,433
Madrigal?

278
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:58,700
Are these people new in town?

279
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:01,600
Because earlier...
thank you.

280
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:04,267
When I was at the store earlier,

281
00:20:04,333 --> 00:20:07,567
the saleslady told me that
a certain Mrs. Madrigal

282
00:20:07,633 --> 00:20:10,100
had bought all the bags
I wanted.

283
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:12,800
Wow.

284
00:20:19,233 --> 00:20:20,500
Thank you, Mr. Lee.

285
00:20:21,133 --> 00:20:23,367
Can we talk in my office?

286
00:20:23,433 --> 00:20:24,267
Sure, Lucho.

287
00:20:24,333 --> 00:20:26,000
Anything you say.

288
00:20:26,067 --> 00:20:28,300
We'd been through a lot
of business together.

289
00:20:29,533 --> 00:20:30,733
Thank you.

290
00:20:34,967 --> 00:20:37,167
Okay, I'll just call you later.

291
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:14,900
Mr. Lee, meet my wife,
Mrs. Madrigal.

292
00:21:17,167 --> 00:21:19,000
It's an honor, Mrs. Madrigal.

293
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:22,967
Pleased to meet you, Mr. Lee.

294
00:21:27,833 --> 00:21:29,233
Where is Eden?

295
00:21:30,333 --> 00:21:32,833
Don't tell me she's locking
herself in her room again.

296
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:34,933
It won't do her any good.

297
00:21:37,100 --> 00:21:38,367
She doesn't want to go
out of her room, Mom.

298
00:21:39,133 --> 00:21:41,833
All she does is hug
our baby's urn.

299
00:21:43,467 --> 00:21:46,433
Maybe she needs to
see a psychiatrist.

300
00:21:47,567 --> 00:21:50,700
She could have postpartum
depression.

301
00:21:50,767 --> 00:21:53,867
Especially in your case
because you lost the baby.

302
00:21:55,433 --> 00:21:57,833
Wait a minute, aren't you
a little overreacting?

303
00:21:57,900 --> 00:21:59,500
You're considering seeing
a psychiatrist already?

304
00:22:00,100 --> 00:22:02,700
She just needs to
get out of her room!

305
00:22:02,767 --> 00:22:04,167
Maybe she needs some...

306
00:22:04,233 --> 00:22:05,233
morning sun.

307
00:22:05,300 --> 00:22:07,467
You know? It's going to do
her a lot of good.

308
00:22:07,533 --> 00:22:09,133
She doesn't need
a psychiatrist.

309
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,367
My God.

310
00:22:10,433 --> 00:22:13,433
She really will lose her sanity

311
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:15,133
if all she does is
stay in her room.

312
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:19,367
I'm going to bring her food.

313
00:22:20,133 --> 00:22:21,867
I'll try to convince her, Mom.

314
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:38,800
Come on, Victor.

315
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:41,033
Did you have to suggest bringing
her to a psychiatrist?

316
00:22:41,633 --> 00:22:43,267
What else can we do?

317
00:22:43,567 --> 00:22:46,167
Let her lose her sanity.

318
00:22:46,233 --> 00:22:48,300
That way, Red will leave her.

319
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:50,200
They lost their child anyway.

320
00:22:50,267 --> 00:22:52,233
What do you want? Do you want
them to make another one?

321
00:22:53,700 --> 00:22:56,833
Tell me, can you accept a child

322
00:22:56,900 --> 00:22:59,833
that is also related to Amanda?

323
00:23:01,333 --> 00:23:05,800
Are you telling me that you're
glad they lost their child?

324
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:18,800
Baby.

325
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:24,967
I want to feel you again.

326
00:23:29,833 --> 00:23:31,800
I miss you.

327
00:23:33,833 --> 00:23:35,967
Where are you?

328
00:23:38,933 --> 00:23:40,100
Where are you, Sweetie?

329
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:55,600
Red!

330
00:23:56,200 --> 00:23:57,900
Red, our baby's alive.

331
00:23:57,967 --> 00:23:59,267
I can hear him!

332
00:23:59,333 --> 00:24:01,000
I hear our baby crying, Red.

333
00:24:06,467 --> 00:24:07,267
Baby.

334
00:24:07,933 --> 00:24:08,733
Red!

335
00:24:09,300 --> 00:24:11,433
Red, our baby's alive.

336
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:14,667
Can you hear it?

337
00:24:15,233 --> 00:24:16,667
Our baby's alive.

338
00:24:16,733 --> 00:24:17,700
He's alive!

339
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:20,967
Red.

340
00:24:23,133 --> 00:24:24,133
This looks nice.

341
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:29,467
Okay. Can I have this
in a size 8, please?

342
00:24:29,567 --> 00:24:30,533
Ma'am, it's been sold.

343
00:24:30,600 --> 00:24:32,633
You have the same shoe
size as Mrs. Madrigal.

344
00:24:34,267 --> 00:24:36,067
Mrs. Madrigal again?

345
00:24:38,133 --> 00:24:41,500
Wait, I'm getting curious
about Mrs. Madrigal.

346
00:24:43,367 --> 00:24:45,833
I think I'd like
to get to meet her.

347
00:24:46,700 --> 00:24:49,500
She's always buying
out everything I want.

348
00:24:50,867 --> 00:24:54,100
She said she was going
to look at other shops.

349
00:24:54,167 --> 00:24:55,233
Here? Now?

350
00:24:55,300 --> 00:24:56,133
Yes, Ma'am.

351
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:58,000
Okay, where could she be?

352
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:05,033
Excuse me.

353
00:25:05,100 --> 00:25:07,367
Do you know Mrs. Madrigal?

354
00:25:07,433 --> 00:25:08,600
She just went out.

355
00:25:08,667 --> 00:25:10,467
She's probably on her
way to the parking area.

356
00:25:11,267 --> 00:25:12,967
At the parking area?

357
00:25:13,033 --> 00:25:13,933
Yes, Ma'am.

358
00:25:18,200 --> 00:25:19,267
That's her.

359
00:25:21,533 --> 00:25:22,200
Thank you.

360
00:25:22,267 --> 00:25:23,333
Thank you!

361
00:25:25,667 --> 00:25:26,767
Mrs. Madrigal?

362
00:25:34,800 --> 00:25:36,067
Surprise!

363
00:25:36,167 --> 00:25:37,667
I don't want this!

364
00:25:37,733 --> 00:25:39,567
I want our baby!

365
00:25:39,633 --> 00:25:43,933
But Eden, we have to accept
that our baby's gone.

366
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,467
Red, our baby is still alive.

367
00:25:45,533 --> 00:25:47,100
Why don't you believe me?

368
00:25:47,167 --> 00:25:48,533
Our baby's still alive!

369
00:25:48,600 --> 00:25:49,900
Why don't you go out?

370
00:25:49,967 --> 00:25:51,533
Go out with your friends.

371
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:52,567
What about Eden?

372
00:25:52,633 --> 00:25:55,467
I think it's better to
give her some space.

373
00:25:55,533 --> 00:25:56,767
Leave her be for now.

374
00:25:56,833 --> 00:25:59,033
I'm really sorry
about your baby.

375
00:25:59,100 --> 00:25:59,867
Is that it?

376
00:25:59,933 --> 00:26:01,467
You won't say I told you so?

377
00:26:01,533 --> 00:26:04,967
I know that you love Eden.

378
00:26:05,033 --> 00:26:05,933
I've moved on.

379
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:08,400
That's what Eden
and I fought about.

380
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:09,667
I know she's hurting,

381
00:26:09,733 --> 00:26:11,700
and I've always been
there for her.

382
00:26:11,767 --> 00:26:13,533
But I'm hurting too.

383
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:15,100
Who's there for me?

384
00:26:15,167 --> 00:26:16,600
Please, don't be mad at Red.

385
00:26:16,667 --> 00:26:18,667
He's been going through a lot.

386
00:26:18,733 --> 00:26:21,733
He even told me that
you're pushing him away.

387
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:23,167
Please, Sabina.

388
00:26:23,233 --> 00:26:26,400
Stop acting as if you care
about our relationship.
